RIYADH:Â The Coalition to Restore Legitimacy in Yemen destroyed two explosive-laden Houthi boats on Wednesday, Saudi Press Agency reported. The coalition said that the militia was planning to use the boats in attacks on oil tankers crossing the Bab Al-Mandab Strait. The attempt to launch the two boats was prepared from Hodeidah Governorate and the Houthi militia is escalating its hostile attacks to target energy sources, the coalition added.